54:12.440 --> 54:14.140
to bring forth limited disclosures.

54:14.320 --> 54:16.460
So TTSA is wacky when you look at it.

54:16.580 --> 54:18.220
You know, Tom DeLonge had numerous,

54:18.320 --> 54:19.640
numerous high level advisors,

54:19.840 --> 54:21.620
whether it was somebody like Lou Elizondo,

54:22.000 --> 54:23.980
a whole history in counterintelligence,

54:24.140 --> 54:25.380
um, guys like Steve Justice

54:25.380 --> 54:26.420
from Lockheed Martin,

54:26.540 --> 54:27.740
high level air force generals.

54:27.740 --> 54:29.160
And these guys were saying,

54:29.320 --> 54:30.760
Hey, you know, all of these,

54:30.920 --> 54:32.140
all of these technologies

54:32.140 --> 54:33.640
are locked up in black budgets,

54:33.640 --> 54:34.680
but we're going to,

54:34.900 --> 54:35.860
we don't really know how to do it,

54:35.880 --> 54:37.000
but we're going to try and make our own

54:37.000 --> 54:37.700
like light craft.

54:37.700 --> 54:38.440
If we're going to try and make

54:38.440 --> 54:39.980
our own ARVs and all that.

54:40.180 --> 54:41.440
So it just seems almost

54:41.440 --> 54:42.480
like a bastardization

54:42.480 --> 54:43.820
of what legacy programs

54:43.820 --> 54:44.560
had doing like an,

54:44.740 --> 54:46.740
like all these guys,

54:46.820 --> 54:47.720
Steve Justice who had worked

54:47.720 --> 54:48.840
in programs or been exposed

54:48.840 --> 54:49.940
to them had amnesia

54:49.940 --> 54:50.920
and they had to kind of start

54:50.920 --> 54:52.460
all over again in the public sector.

54:53.240 --> 54:53.380
There were,

54:53.380 --> 54:55.060
there were clearly guys involved

54:55.060 --> 54:56.960
in that who had ulterior motives.

54:56.960 --> 54:58.020
And then I do think,

54:58.180 --> 54:59.680
I think, you know,

54:59.680 --> 55:01.600
some people don't give Tom DeLonge

55:01.600 --> 55:03.420
enough credit for modern disclosure.

55:03.980 --> 55:05.620
Because like so many people

55:05.620 --> 55:07.260
just wouldn't even be into the subject.

55:07.260 --> 55:08.240
I think if it weren't

55:08.240 --> 55:09.900
for a lot of what he got out.

55:09.980 --> 55:12.740
And I do think he on his own

55:12.740 --> 55:14.840
organically made a ton of connections,

55:15.060 --> 55:16.320
poked the bear a lot

55:16.320 --> 55:19.000
to the effect of a lot of these guys

55:19.000 --> 55:20.120
coming out to him.

55:20.240 --> 55:20.980
And he kind of,

55:21.100 --> 55:21.760
I think,

55:22.000 --> 55:23.500
put a lot of this stuff together.

55:23.700 --> 55:24.160
And so, yeah,

55:24.200 --> 55:24.400
maybe,

55:24.400 --> 55:25.020
maybe they're,

55:25.020 --> 55:25.520
you know,

55:25.800 --> 55:26.560
ulterior motives

55:26.560 --> 55:27.880
with some of the people involved.

55:28.240 --> 55:30.060
But I don't think Tom had ulterior motives.

55:30.120 --> 55:31.300
I think he had very genuine,

55:31.860 --> 55:32.180
you know.

55:32.340 --> 55:33.220
He was a trailblazer.

55:33.340 --> 55:34.140
Yeah, I think so.

55:34.280 --> 55:34.440
Yeah.

55:34.600 --> 55:35.740
I also think a strong argument

55:35.740 --> 55:36.240
can be made.

55:36.320 --> 55:38.500
He was exposed to some pretty radical stuff,

55:38.560 --> 55:39.660
whether this was authorized

55:39.660 --> 55:41.720
or unauthorized disclosures.

55:42.040 --> 55:43.280
If you look at his appearance

55:43.280 --> 55:45.240
on Joe Rogan back in 2017,

55:45.400 --> 55:46.240
October of 2017,

55:46.240 --> 55:47.720
this was like the radical time

55:47.720 --> 55:48.360
that he came out

55:48.360 --> 55:49.480
and talked about TTSA.

55:50.160 --> 55:50.620
There's something

55:50.620 --> 55:51.680
that really caught my eye there.

55:51.680 --> 55:53.020
And I think a strong argument

55:53.020 --> 55:53.720
can be made.

55:54.140 --> 55:55.160
Tom DeLonge was exposed

55:55.160 --> 55:56.640
to elements of

55:56.640 --> 55:57.740
Immaculate Constellation.

55:58.140 --> 55:58.160
Yeah.

55:58.260 --> 55:58.780
Oh, interesting.

55:59.000 --> 56:00.220
We know Immaculate Constellation

56:00.220 --> 56:02.620
as the USAT Matthew Brown

56:02.620 --> 56:03.520
was exposed to

56:03.520 --> 56:05.380
that began in 2017

56:05.380 --> 56:06.420
that utilized

56:06.420 --> 56:09.240
U.S. intelligence platforms,

56:09.380 --> 56:10.180
overhead platforms,

56:10.740 --> 56:11.580
implying NRO

56:11.580 --> 56:12.620
with spy satellites

56:12.620 --> 56:13.760
