in 1961

01:01:15.780 --> 01:01:16.920
after a shoot-down

01:01:16.920 --> 01:01:17.860
of a U-2 spy plane

01:01:17.860 --> 01:01:19.080
over denied airspace

01:01:19.080 --> 01:01:19.920
in the Soviet Union,

01:01:20.360 --> 01:01:21.940
the NRO had co-directors,

01:01:22.040 --> 01:01:22.700
one from the DOD,

01:01:22.780 --> 01:01:23.420
one from the IC.

01:01:23.620 --> 01:01:23.800
Yep.

01:01:23.940 --> 01:01:24.880
And it's weird

01:01:24.880 --> 01:01:25.480
that the CIA

01:01:25.480 --> 01:01:26.200
seems to have a little

01:01:26.200 --> 01:01:26.820
tug of war

01:01:26.820 --> 01:01:28.240
over any lately founded

01:01:28.240 --> 01:01:29.540
U.S. intelligence agency.

01:01:29.660 --> 01:01:30.480
Same thing with the NRO,

01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:31.640
founded in 1969.

01:01:32.020 --> 01:01:33.160
Up until 1972,

01:01:33.160 --> 01:01:34.520
there was a huge tug of war

01:01:34.520 --> 01:01:35.920
between the Navy and CIA,

01:01:36.180 --> 01:01:37.380
specifically the DS&T,

01:01:37.520 --> 01:01:39.300
over who controls

01:01:39.300 --> 01:01:39.800
the NRO.

01:01:40.220 --> 01:01:40.720
And then, of course,

01:01:40.800 --> 01:01:41.900
Bobby Reinhardt takes over

01:01:41.900 --> 01:01:44.380
and he's just agency

01:01:44.380 --> 01:01:45.080
out the wazoo.

01:01:45.260 --> 01:01:45.800
So, yeah,

01:01:46.000 --> 01:01:47.400
further interesting parallels

01:01:47.400 --> 01:01:47.880
between that.

01:01:47.940 --> 01:01:48.420
Richard Bissell

01:01:48.420 --> 01:01:49.340
is an interesting person.

01:01:49.640 --> 01:01:51.220
I'm particularly fond of,

01:01:51.240 --> 01:01:52.480
and I think you probably are too,

01:01:52.580 --> 01:01:53.320
of Richard Bissell

01:01:53.320 --> 01:01:54.960
allegedly briefing Malmgren

01:01:54.960 --> 01:01:56.500
on otherworldly technologies,

01:01:56.640 --> 01:01:57.300
as we know,

01:01:57.360 --> 01:01:58.320
our buddy Randy Anderson,

01:01:58.740 --> 01:02:00.000
off-world technologies division

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:01.220
under the Naval Surface

01:02:01.220 --> 01:02:02.080
Warfare Center crane.

01:02:02.080 --> 01:02:02.940
Yeah, yeah,

01:02:03.020 --> 01:02:04.080
there definitely seems like

01:02:04.080 --> 01:02:05.180
something might line up there.

01:02:05.500 --> 01:02:06.440
What do you think of,

01:02:06.440 --> 01:02:06.700
you know,

01:02:06.780 --> 01:02:07.640
Malmgren's testimony?

01:02:07.760 --> 01:02:08.720
Because I did that interview,

01:02:08.720 --> 01:02:10.440
and I honestly

01:02:10.440 --> 01:02:11.200
would have expected

01:02:11.200 --> 01:02:12.500
that to have been picked up

01:02:12.500 --> 01:02:13.240
by, like, you know,

01:02:13.360 --> 01:02:14.760
mainstream media,

01:02:14.760 --> 01:02:16.020
because you have a guy

01:02:16.020 --> 01:02:17.460
who is a presidential advisor

01:02:17.460 --> 01:02:18.820
for JFK, LBJ,

01:02:18.940 --> 01:02:19.580
Nixon, and Ford.

01:02:19.660 --> 01:02:20.160
You could argue

01:02:20.160 --> 01:02:21.940
with his level of seniority

01:02:21.940 --> 01:02:22.660
with, you know,

01:02:22.920 --> 01:02:24.320
JFK specifically,

01:02:24.560 --> 01:02:25.360
but he admitted

01:02:25.360 --> 01:02:26.500
that, like, you know,

01:02:26.520 --> 01:02:27.460
he didn't deal

01:02:27.460 --> 01:02:29.200
a ton with JFK directly.

01:02:29.320 --> 01:02:30.420
He dealt more

01:02:30.420 --> 01:02:31.440
with Shriver or whatever.

01:02:32.080 --> 01:02:33.360
And then you can't really

01:02:33.360 --> 01:02:34.340
argue with his, you know,

01:02:34.420 --> 01:02:35.720
connections with the other presidents.

01:02:35.720 --> 01:02:38.020
I think he rose in seniority,

01:02:38.180 --> 01:02:39.020
you know,

01:02:39.020 --> 01:02:39.940
as time went on.

01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:40.120
Yeah.

01:02:40.440 --> 01:02:41.600
Clearly was connected

01:02:41.600 --> 01:02:43.200
at the highest levels

01:02:43.200 --> 01:02:43.660
of government.

01:02:43.660 --> 01:02:45.120
To me, you know,

01:02:45.520 --> 01:02:46.640
and I've met a lot of, like,

01:02:46.700 --> 01:02:47.960
I think pretty impressive people,

01:02:48.060 --> 01:02:49.180
like, just pattern matched

01:02:49.180 --> 01:02:50.300
to somebody who had a map

01:02:50.300 --> 01:02:51.620
of the world in his head

01:02:51.620 --> 01:02:53.140
was a total kind of

01:02:53.140 --> 01:02:54.480
Kissinger type, you know,

01:02:54.540 --> 01:02:56.660
maybe without the bad vibes

01:02:56.660 --> 01:02:57.740
that Kissinger had,

01:02:57.740 --> 01:03:00.360
you know, the desire

01:03:00.360 --> 01:03:01.520
to create destruction

01:03:01.520 --> 01:03:02.260
and manipulate.

01:03:02.460 --> 01:03:03.360
I think in some ways

01:03:03.360 --> 01:03:04.200
he was kind of, like,

01:03:04.780 --> 01:03:06.400
the opposite of Kissinger.

01:03:06.520 --> 01:03:07.280
And he was actually,

01:03:07.660 --> 01:03:09.360
you know, likely, I think,

01:03:09.740 --> 01:03:10.280
you know,

01:03:10.440 --> 01:03:11.820
I think he was CIA.

01:03:12.200 --> 01:03:12.360
Yeah.

01:03:12.440 --> 01:03:14.140
And I think he was likely

01:03:14.140 --> 01:03:15.680
actually appointed

01:03:15.680 --> 01:03:17.560
to kind of restrain

01:03:17.560 --> 01:03:18.700
Kissinger in many ways.

01:03:18.780 --> 01:03:19.340
Like, he was kind of,

01:03:19.380 --> 01:03:20.840
he was tagged with

01:03:20.840 --> 01:03:22.320
reigning in Kissinger,

01:03:22.320 --> 01:03:23.240
who was seen as this

01:03:23.240 --> 01:03:24.300
kind of rogue guy.

01:03:24.740 --> 01:03:25.900
So what do you think

01:03:25.900 --> 01:03:26.880
of his testimony?

01:03:26.880 --> 01:03:28.260
Because there are some people

01:03:28.260 --> 01:03:29.420
who've, I think that's

01:03:29.420 --> 01:03:30.860
kind of this coordinated job,

01:03:30.960 --> 01:03:31.540
but, like, some people

01:03:31.540 --> 01:03:32.960
have come out and attacked him

01:03:32.960 --> 01:03:34.540
since that interview.

01:03:34.920 --> 01:03:36.380
I think Malmgren was likely CIA

01:03:36.380 --> 01:03:37.840
and his position at the IDA

01:03:37.840 --> 01:03:38.520
was a knocker,

01:03:38.580 --> 01:03:39.340
non-official cover,

01:03:39.460 --> 01:03:40.680
which is a very common

01:03:40.680 --> 01:03:43.780
thing for agency stuff.

01:03:43.960 --> 01:03:44.120
Yeah.

01:03:44.520 --> 01:03:45.520
I hope that,

01:03:45.620 --> 01:03:46.460
I think over time

01:03:46.460 --> 01:03:47.440
that Malmgren's testimony

01:03:47.440 --> 01:03:48.860
is going to age like fine wine.

01:03:49.180 --> 01:03:50.400
I mean, I was re-listening

01:03:50.400 --> 01:03:52.180
to your project with him

01:03:52.180 --> 01:03:53.380
just for one of my projects,

01:03:53.380 --> 01:03:56.640
and I was particularly intrigued

01:03:56.640 --> 01:03:58.220
when he is talking about

01:03:58.220 --> 01:04:00.220
intelligence communities

01:04:00.220 --> 01:04:02.200
and how intelligence communities

01:04:02.200 --> 01:04:03.500
have essentially found a way

01:04:03.500 --> 01:04:04.640
to fund themselves,

01:04:04.840 --> 01:04:05.660
and so they don't adhere

01:04:05.660 --> 01:04:07.060
to traditional oversight channels

01:04:07.060 --> 01:04:07.780
because they basically

01:04:07.780 --> 01:04:08.480
fund themselves.

01:04:08.820 --> 01:04:09.780
This comports exactly

01:04:09.780 --> 01:04:10.700
with what I think

01:04:10.700 --> 01:04:11.640
about institutions

01:04:11.640 --> 01:04:12.280
like the NRO

01:04:12.280 --> 01:04:13.540
or other intelligence agencies

01:04:13.540 --> 01:04:14.740
and UFO legacy programs.

01:04:15.120 --> 01:04:16.160
1994, 1995,

01:04:16.380 --> 01:04:17.460
they can use carryover funds

01:04:17.460 --> 01:04:18.080
basically to do

01:04:18.080 --> 01:04:19.020
whatever the heck they want.

01:04:19.020 --> 01:04:20.840
I also think that,

01:04:20.940 --> 01:04:22.380
I hope the 1962

01:04:22.380 --> 01:04:23.900
Bluegill Triple Prime

01:04:23.900 --> 01:04:24.560
nuclear test

01:04:24.560 --> 01:04:25.380
starts to get revisited

01:04:25.380 --> 01:04:26.360
with what Malmgren said,

01:04:26.440 --> 01:04:26.700
of course,

01:04:26.800 --> 01:04:27.400
that was a,

01:04:28.160 --> 01:04:28.500
was that,

01:04:28.680 --> 01:04:29.280
were those tests

01:04:29.280 --> 01:04:30.220
over Bikini Atoll?

01:04:30.380 --> 01:04:31.100
Where were those?

01:04:31.320 --> 01:04:32.100
Johnston Atoll.

01:04:32.160 --> 01:04:32.620
Yes, yes, yes.

01:04:32.620 --> 01:04:33.360
Just came to me, yeah.

01:04:33.640 --> 01:04:34.160
I know there's been

01:04:34.160 --> 01:04:34.660
some discussion

01:04:34.660 --> 01:04:35.520
on whether that was

01:04:35.520 --> 01:04:36.540
a targeting pod

01:04:36.540 --> 01:04:37.880
or something that

01:04:37.880 --> 01:04:38.900
was knocked out

01:04:38.900 --> 01:04:39.800
by the residual EMP

01:04:39.800 --> 01:04:40.780
of the nuclear blast

01:04:40.780 --> 01:04:42.120
when Malmgren stated

01:04:42.120 --> 01:04:43.520
that Bissell briefed him

01:04:43.520 --> 01:04:44.460
on that being a UFO.

01:04:44.960 --> 01:04:45.920
I think Jeff Cruikshank

01:04:45.920 --> 01:04:47.000
has done some incredible work

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:47.860
and is still to this day

01:04:47.860 --> 01:04:48.520
making the argument

01:04:48.520 --> 01:04:49.820
that that was a UFO

01:04:49.820 --> 01:04:50.980
recovered by the USS,

01:04:51.380 --> 01:04:52.420
I think it was in Gage.

01:04:52.660 --> 01:04:52.880
Yeah.

01:04:53.680 --> 01:04:54.400
What's interesting

01:04:54.400 --> 01:04:55.600
about that testimony

01:04:55.600 --> 01:04:57.100
is those tests

01:04:57.100 --> 01:04:57.860
were a,

01:04:58.040 --> 01:04:59.220
were conducted

01:04:59.220 --> 01:04:59.920
under the,

01:05:00.580 --> 01:05:03.240
a evolution agency

01:05:03.240 --> 01:05:04.320
of the AFSWP,

01:05:04.420 --> 01:05:04.940
the Armed Forces

01:05:04.940 --> 01:05:05.820
Special Weapons Project,

01:05:05.960 --> 01:05:06.340
which eventually

01:05:06.340 --> 01:05:06.860
became DITRA.

01:05:06.940 --> 01:05:07.420
I can't remember

01:05:07.420 --> 01:05:08.580
the agency specifically.

01:05:09.860 --> 01:05:10.620
AFSWP went through

01:05:10.620 --> 01:05:11.720
like eight or nine iterations

01:05:11.720 --> 01:05:13.520
before it became DITRA.

01:05:13.740 --> 01:05:14.620
Sorry, not eight or nine,

01:05:14.660 --> 01:05:15.400
that's an exaggeration,

01:05:15.480 --> 01:05:16.240
like four or five.

01:05:16.380 --> 01:05:16.540
Yeah.

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:18.260
But that agency

01:05:18.260 --> 01:05:19.200
did the testing.

01:05:19.400 --> 01:05:19.500
Yeah.

01:05:19.740 --> 01:05:20.080
Really?

01:05:20.200 --> 01:05:20.340
Yeah.

01:05:20.380 --> 01:05:21.600
And Sandia supplied

01:05:21.600 --> 01:05:22.480
like the,

01:05:22.480 --> 01:05:24.280
the specific rocket payload

01:05:24.280 --> 01:05:25.660
for that testing and such.

01:05:25.920 --> 01:05:26.760
But what's interesting to me

01:05:26.760 --> 01:05:27.840
is when Dylan Borland

01:05:27.840 --> 01:05:28.480
talks about old

01:05:28.480 --> 01:05:29.860
Atomic Energy Commission records,

01:05:29.960 --> 01:05:30.620
talking about,

01:05:30.680 --> 01:05:32.860
concluding that UFOs

01:05:32.860 --> 01:05:34.040
are extraterrestrial vehicles

01:05:34.040 --> 01:05:36.020
based upon

01:05:36.020 --> 01:05:37.120
the Atomic Energy Commission.

01:05:37.240 --> 01:05:37.300
I,

01:05:37.340 --> 01:05:38.260
I wonder if,

01:05:38.320 --> 01:05:39.260
if part of those records

01:05:39.260 --> 01:05:40.620
adhere to the AFSWP

01:05:40.620 --> 01:05:41.240
before it came,

01:05:41.480 --> 01:05:42.140
became DITRA

01:05:42.140 --> 01:05:44.380
recording that crash.

01:05:44.380 --> 01:05:44.620
Yeah.

01:05:44.740 --> 01:05:45.300
And the whole,

01:05:45.480 --> 01:05:45.680
I mean,

01:05:45.740 --> 01:05:46.500
so there's this guy,

01:05:46.620 --> 01:05:46.880
you know,

01:05:46.940 --> 01:05:47.600
D. Dean Johnson

01:05:47.600 --> 01:05:48.100
who took,

01:05:48.340 --> 01:05:48.480
you know,

01:05:48.480 --> 01:05:49.100
tried to do this

01:05:49.100 --> 01:05:50.140
like takedown of Malmgren

01:05:50.140 --> 01:05:51.020
and the whole takedown

01:05:51.020 --> 01:05:51.540
was like,

01:05:51.860 --> 01:05:52.060
you know,

01:05:52.080 --> 01:05:52.720
he couldn't have held

01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:53.440
the queue clearance,

01:05:53.620 --> 01:05:55.140
which you wouldn't be able

01:05:55.140 --> 01:05:55.760
to figure out

01:05:55.760 --> 01:05:56.920
through the FBI at all

01:05:56.920 --> 01:05:57.820
if the guy was CIA.

01:05:58.080 --> 01:05:58.800
You just wouldn't.

01:05:59.160 --> 01:05:59.560
And especially

01:05:59.560 --> 01:06:01.520
if you're a non-official cover CIA,

01:06:01.740 --> 01:06:02.540
there's just no way.

01:06:03.060 --> 01:06:03.840
And so I think

01:06:03.840 --> 01:06:05.440
a lot of those points

01:06:05.440 --> 01:06:06.380
are sort of rendered moot.

01:06:06.440 --> 01:06:07.180
And then you could say,

01:06:07.340 --> 01:06:07.860
well,

01:06:07.880 --> 01:06:08.620
he wasn't CIA,

01:06:08.880 --> 01:06:09.420
but it's like,

01:06:09.480 --> 01:06:10.780
if you read the tea leaves

01:06:10.780 --> 01:06:11.240
on the interview,

01:06:11.240 --> 01:06:12.560
he's saying he handled

01:06:12.560 --> 01:06:13.700
the presidential daily brief.

01:06:13.800 --> 01:06:14.740
That's a CIA thing.

01:06:14.800 --> 01:06:15.760
He's saying he's best friends

01:06:15.760 --> 01:06:17.120
with Tom Farmer,

01:06:17.280 --> 01:06:17.900
who happened to be

01:06:17.900 --> 01:06:18.560
the general counsel

01:06:18.560 --> 01:06:19.040
of the CIA.

01:06:19.740 --> 01:06:21.420
He had Paul Mellon's

01:06:21.420 --> 01:06:22.300
walking stick

01:06:22.300 --> 01:06:23.300
in the interview

01:06:23.300 --> 01:06:24.460
and I'm holding it

01:06:24.460 --> 01:06:25.420
for half the time

01:06:25.420 --> 01:06:26.000
in the interview

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:26.420
or whatever

01:06:26.420 --> 01:06:27.420
because I wanted to see it.

01:06:27.480 --> 01:06:29.280
And he had it offhand

01:06:29.280 --> 01:06:30.540
just in his apartment.

01:06:30.780 --> 01:06:32.000
Does it represent anything?

01:06:32.220 --> 01:06:33.420
It looks very unique.

01:06:34.380 --> 01:06:34.640
Well,

01:06:34.820 --> 01:06:35.960
he has a lot of power.

01:06:37.920 --> 01:06:39.220
So Paul Mellon's

01:06:39.220 --> 01:06:39.520
the founder,

01:06:39.520 --> 01:06:40.160
one of the founders

01:06:40.160 --> 01:06:40.740
of the CIA.

01:06:41.320 --> 01:06:42.060
So like,

01:06:42.060 --> 01:06:43.120
I don't know.

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:44.160
You got to read the

01:06:44.160 --> 01:06:45.820
read the kind of tea leaves

01:06:45.820 --> 01:06:46.320
on it.

01:06:47.180 --> 01:06:47.740
You know,

01:06:47.760 --> 01:06:49.100
and I kind of,

01:06:49.100 --> 01:06:50.120
I think,

01:06:50.220 --> 01:06:51.160
figured that out

01:06:51.160 --> 01:06:52.520
through kind of basic research.

01:06:52.660 --> 01:06:52.800
You know,

01:06:52.820 --> 01:06:53.480
he's at Oxford.

01:06:53.740 --> 01:06:54.200
He's Yale.

01:06:54.440 --> 01:06:54.600
You know,

01:06:54.640 --> 01:06:56.300
it's like Richard Bissell

01:06:56.300 --> 01:06:56.880
is your mentor.

01:06:57.100 --> 01:06:57.900
He's deputy director.

01:06:57.980 --> 01:06:58.440
He's number two

01:06:58.440 --> 01:06:59.360
in the entire CIA.

01:06:59.560 --> 01:07:00.460
We have Richard Bissell

01:07:00.460 --> 01:07:01.380
all over his diary.

01:07:01.760 --> 01:07:02.080
All over it.

01:07:02.140 --> 01:07:03.320
So it's like so clear

01:07:03.320 --> 01:07:04.520
to me that he was CIA.

01:07:04.960 --> 01:07:05.680
And then,

01:07:05.740 --> 01:07:06.180
I don't know,

01:07:06.180 --> 01:07:06.980
I felt like

01:07:06.980 --> 01:07:08.840
maybe it was hard

01:07:08.840 --> 01:07:09.840
for me to break

01:07:09.840 --> 01:07:11.880
this gentlemanly oath

01:07:11.880 --> 01:07:12.400
that he had,

01:07:12.500 --> 01:07:13.860
he was kind of breaking it

01:07:13.860 --> 01:07:14.460
on his own.

01:07:14.660 --> 01:07:14.820
You know,

01:07:14.880 --> 01:07:15.920
he clearly was breaking it

01:07:15.920 --> 01:07:17.020
in the UFO context,

01:07:17.020 --> 01:07:18.140
but I felt weird

01:07:18.140 --> 01:07:19.500
explicitly outing him.

01:07:19.600 --> 01:07:19.760
Yeah.

01:07:19.900 --> 01:07:20.460
He's saying,

01:07:20.560 --> 01:07:20.700
hey,

01:07:20.740 --> 01:07:21.300
are you CIA?

01:07:21.640 --> 01:07:21.940
Yeah.

01:07:22.200 --> 01:07:22.460
Yeah.

01:07:22.560 --> 01:07:23.560
And it's the guy's like,

01:07:23.660 --> 01:07:23.900
you know,

01:07:23.980 --> 01:07:24.920
literally by the time

01:07:24.920 --> 01:07:25.480
we had put it out,

01:07:25.540 --> 01:07:26.640
he had passed away,

01:07:26.760 --> 01:07:27.080
sadly.

01:07:27.220 --> 01:07:27.720
And so like,

01:07:27.800 --> 01:07:28.720
I just didn't feel

01:07:28.720 --> 01:07:29.500
like it was my place,

01:07:29.600 --> 01:07:30.860
but I did insert

01:07:30.860 --> 01:07:31.460
a little thing

01:07:31.460 --> 01:07:32.100
at the very beginning

01:07:32.100 --> 01:07:32.620
in the monologue

